07207nam a22011415i 9783035622034DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20202020sz     fo  d z      eng d  a2020934141  a97830356220347 a10.1515/97830356220342doi  a(DE-B1597)546553  a(OCoLC)1178769499  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH00aHT241b.D47 2020. 7aDES0000002bisacsh00aDesigning Sustainable Cities :bManageable Approaches to Make Urban Spaces Better /ced. by Karl Stocker, Sigrid Bürstmayr.  a23,5 x 19,5 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (152 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tFOREWORD -- tContents -- tDesigning the World for the Better -- tInclusive Design in Contemporary Detroit -- tUrban Oases. Can Cities of the Future Function like Forests? -- tInterior Architecture in Sustainable Cities -- tThe Potential of Alternative Architecture for an Ecologically Driven and Socially Engaged Istanbul -- tSustainable Istanbul: Studies for an Urban Design Guide; Participation— Policy—Scope -- tMexico City: New Collective Approaches to Fix a Broken City -- tDesign for Sustainability: Questioning Our Material Culture -- tBiographies0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDa 2050 bereits 70 % der Menschheit in Städten leben wird, ist das Zukunftsthema "nachhaltige Stadtgestaltung" für die UNESCO Cities of Design ein wichtiger Schwerpunkt. Unter dem Gesichtspunkt, dass Design einen substanziellen Beitrag zur positiven Veränderung in Umwelt- und Sozialfragen zu leisten vermag, stellt das Buch sieben Beispiele vor, die als Anregung zur Nachahmung zu verstehen sind: sie zeigen Maßnahmen und Problemanalysen für die Städte Detroit, Graz, Istanbul, Mexico City und Puebla, sowie Projekte, die ortsungebunden anwendbar sind. Thematisiert werden u. a. die Effizienz von Zertifikaten, Klimainstallationen für Stadträume und neue ökologische, architektonische und soziologische Konzepte für Megastädte. Ein Lesebuch für Akteurinnen und Akteure an der Schnittstelle von Sozio-Design und Städtebau.  aIn view of the fact that, by 2050, 70% of the world’s population will live in cities, the subject of "sustainable urban design" is an important issue for UNESCO’s Cities of Design. Taking into account that urban design can make a significant contribution to positive changes in environmental and social matters, the book presents seven inspirational examples for copying; included are analyses and measures for the cities of Detroit, Graz, Istanbul, Mexico City, and Puebla, as well as non-location bound projects. The authors investigate the efficiency of certificates, climate installations for urban spaces, and new ecological, architectural, and sociological concepts for mega-cities. A reader for stakeholders at the interface of social and urban design.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aSustainable urban development. 4aCity. 4aEnvironment. 4aGreen Design. 4aSocial Design. 4aUrban Sustainability. 4aUrban. 7aDESIGN / General.2bisacsh1 aArabacıoğlu, Burcin Cem.1 aBreathe Earth Collective, .1 aBürstmayr, Sigrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBürstmayr, Sigrid, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCem Arabacıoğlu, Burçin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCiravoğlu, Ayşen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCiravoğlu, Ayşen.1 aDraus, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDraus, Paul.1 aMoreno Valle, Paulina Cornejo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPolatoğlu, Ciğdem.1 aPolatoğlu, Çiğdem, econtributor.4ctb4https://i